com.im.njams.sdk.utils

Interface ClasspathValidator

  • All Known Subinterfaces:
    Receiver, Sender, ShareableReceiver
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    AbstractReceiver, AbstractSender, HttpReceiver, HttpSender, HttpsSender, JmsReceiver, JmsSender, NjamsSender, SharedJmsReceiver

    public interface ClasspathValidator
    This interface can be used to validate if the given libraries are in the classpath.
    Version:
    4.0.5
    Author:
    krautenberg@integrationmatters.com

    • Method Summary

      All Methods Instance Methods Default Methods 
      Modifier and Type Method and Description
      default String[] librariesToCheck()
      This method gets all libraries that need to be checked.
      default void validate()
      Per default this method validates that libraries that are returned by librariesToCheck are available in the classpath.

    • Method Detail

      • validate

        default void validate()
               throws ClassNotFoundException
        Per default this method validates that libraries that are returned by librariesToCheck are available in the classpath.
        Throws:
        ClassNotFoundException - This exception is thrown if any class is not found.

      • librariesToCheck

        default String[] librariesToCheck()
        This method gets all libraries that need to be checked. As default, it returns null.
        Returns:
        An array of Strings of fully qualified class names.
